Socio-demographic information in the Hamilton CMA.

Source: R/envsocty3LT3-package.R
hamilton_demo_taz.Rd

A table with socio-demographicinformation from the Transportation Tomorrow Survey by traffic analysis zone. These data are for 2016.

data(hamilton_demo_taz)

Format

A data frame with 297 rows and 15 variables:

GTA06

Unique identifier of zone in the GTA06 system

Population

Population in traffic analysis zone

Worked_in_2010_Full_time

Number of peple in traffic analysis zones that had were employed full time and worked away from home in 2010

Worked_in_2010_Part_time

Number of peple in traffic analysis zones that had were employed part time and worked away from home in 2010

Worked_at_home

Number of peple in traffic analysis zones that worked from home in 2010

Pop_Density

Population density of traffic analysis zone in persons/sq.km

Median_Age

Median age of the population in traffic analysis zone

Family_Size_2

Number of families of size 2 in the traffic analysis zone

Family_Size_3

Number of families of size 3 in the traffic analysis zone

Family_Size_4

Number of families of size 4 in the traffic analysis zone

Family_Size_5_more

Number of families of size 5 or more in the traffic analysis zone

Median_income

Median income of households in traffic analysis zone

Average_income

Average income of households in traffic analysis zone

Employment_rate

Employment rate in traffic analysis zone

Unemployment_rate

Unemployment rate in traffic analysis zone

Median_commuting_duration

Median duration in minutes of commute to work trips that originated in traffic analysis zone

Source

Transportation Tomorrow Survey (http://dmg.utoronto.ca/transportation-tomorrow-survey/tts-introduction)

 data(hamilton_demo_taz)
